ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: I would absolutely recommend this course to fellow students. The course is, as it purports to be, a survey of the history of literary theory. It is all but necessary for students interested in literary studies as it presents various modes of thinking about texts. Furthermore, it presents a sort of critical lexicon which, even if not helpful for your writing, say if you subscribe to a different critical framework, certainly makes one's reading more beneficial as it allows you to gain access to a wide array of critical scholarship.
The most suitable course for interning the world of literary theory.
